'''''The Chollima''''' ({{korean|context=north|천리마|千里馬}}) is a monthly educational magazine of the [[North Korea|Democratic People's Republic of Korea]].<ref name="Seoul2002">{{cite book|author=Yonhap News Agency, Seoul|title=North Korea Handbook|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JIlh9nNeadMC&pg=PA425|accessdate=3 September 2014|date=27 December 2002|publisher=M.E. Sharpe|isbn=978-0-7656-3523-5|page=425}}</ref> It was first published in January 1959,<ref name=kcna>{{cite web|title=Chollima, Magazine Popular in DPRK|url=http://kcnawatch.nknews.org/article/bbo9|publisher=KCNA Watch|accessdate=3 September 2014|date=22 January 2014}}</ref> initially to support the [[Chollima Movement]]. The publisher is the ''Chollima'' Editing Committee of the [[Art and Literature Publishing House]]. Unlike most other magazines in the country, it is targeted at the general public.<ref name="Seoul2002"/>
