The '''scholarships in Taiwan''' include [[scholarship]]s for pursuing degrees ([[bachelor degree|bachelor]], [[master degree|master]] or [[PhD]]), academic exchange, conducting research, learning [[Mandarin language|Mandarin]] and experiencing culture in [[Taiwan]]. They are mostly funded by the Taiwanese government, [[List of universities in Taiwan|universities]] and [[Academia Sinica]], but also by non-profit foundations.
== Overview == The Taiwan Fellowships & Scholarships (TAFS) program is a joint governmental initiative ([[Ministry of Science and Technology (Taiwan)|Ministry of Science and Technology]], [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Taiwan)|Ministry of Foreign Affairs]] (MOFA), [[Ministry of Education (Taiwan)|Ministry of Education]] (MOE), [[Ministry of Culture (Taiwan)|Ministry of Culture]] and [[Ministry of Economic Affairs (Taiwan)|Ministry of Economic Affairs]]) aimed to promote exchange and friendships between Taiwan and the global community. The TAFS comprises awards in three categories: scholarships for Degree, fellowships for research and Huayu (Mandarin) Enrichment Scholarships. Approximately 1,250 TAFS grants are provided annually for undergraduate and postgraduate students as well as researchers across the world to study or to conduct advanced research in Taiwan.<ref>*[http://tafs.mofa.gov.tw/Default.aspx?loc=en Taiwan Fellowships and Scholarships (TAFS)]</ref>
