== Short-term exchange == Fellowships are available for researchers from all fields. Some, however, are limited to only [[Taiwan studies]] and [[sinology]]. The TIGP International Internship Program is available for two-month research stay in [[Academia Sinica]]. {|class=wikitable !Program||Financial assistance ||Additional benefits ||Duration ||Eligibility |- |TIGP International Internship Program<ref>[https://db1x.sinica.edu.tw/tigpSummer/index.php TIGP International Internship Program]</ref>|| [[NT$]]30,000/month || round-trip flight ticket, basic Mandarin course||two months ||pre-doctoral, non-Taiwanese nationals |- |Short Term Research Award<ref>[http://edu.law.moe.gov.tw/EngLawContent.aspx?Type=E&id=235 Short Term Research Award]</ref>|| [[NT$]]25,000/month for PhD students, [[NT$]]40,000/month for postdocs || round-trip flight ticket ||two to six months ||non-Taiwanese nationals |- |MOE APEC Scholarship<ref>[http://edu.law.moe.gov.tw/EngLawContent.aspx?Type=E&id=234 MOE APEC Scholarship]</ref>|| [[NT$]]25,000/month for PhD students, [[NT$]]40,000/month for postdocs || round-trip flight ticket ||two to six months || from [[APEC]] member states |- |Taiwan Summer Institute Program (MOST and [[German Academic Exchange Service|DAAD]])<ref>[https://www.daad.de/ausland/studieren/stipendium/de/70-stipendien-finden-und-bewerben/?detail=50745820 Taiwan Summer Institute Program]</ref>|| [[€]]900/month || round-trip flight ticket, insurances||two months || Students (natural sciences or engineering) in Germany that have a bachelor degree |- |}
