{{infobox pageant titleholder | name = Vincenza Carrieri-Russo | image = Vincenza walking the Runway at Miss Unites States in DC.JPG | alt = | caption = Vincenza Carrieri-Russo | birth_name = | birth_date = June 10, 1984 <!--{{Birth date and age|1984|06|10}}--> | birth_place = [[Newark, Delaware]], United States | alma_mater = [[University of Delaware]] | occupation = | height = {{height|ft=5|in=8}} | weight = | measurements = | skin_color = | hair_color = Brown | eye_color = Blue | dress_size = | collar = | suit = | shoe_size = | title = [[Miss Delaware USA]] 2008 | competitions = [[Miss USA 2008]] | spouse = | children = | homepage = http://www.vincenzacarrierirusso.com | signature = }} '''Vincenza Carrieri-Russo''' (born June 10, 1984) is a model, actress, entrepreneur and [[beauty pageant]] titleholder from [[Newark, Delaware]].<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=http://ireport.cnn.com/docs/DOC-1078249|title=Miss Delaware USA 2008: Vincenza Carrieri-Russo Speaks About Life After Pageantry|last=Diggs|first=Krystol|date=25 January 2014|work=|publisher=CNN iReport|access-date=|via=}}</ref>
Carrieri-Russo was [[Miss Delaware USA]] 2008 and represented [[Delaware]] at the [[Miss USA 2008]] pageant.<ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=http://www.newarkpostonline.com/news/local/article_c8f8a9f8-0337-5338-b7e2-674a07e4722c.html|title=Meet Miss Delaware USA|last=Neff|first=Christine|date=31 December 2007|work=|newspaper=Newark Post|access-date=|via=}}</ref> She also competed at [[Miss United States]] 2014. Currently she works as a restaurateur alongside her sister.<ref name=":2">{{Cite news|url=http://www.delawareonline.com/story/secondhelpings/2014/10/28/family-run-italian-bistro-opens-on-marsh-road/18054363/|title=Family-run Italian bistro opens on Marsh Road|last=Talorico|first=Patricia|date=28 October 2014|work=|newspaper=The News-Journal|access-date=|via=}}</ref>
== Biography == Carrieri-Russo attended [[Alexis I. duPont High School]] and is a graduate of [[University of Delaware]] with a major in English and concentration in literary studies.<ref name=":3">{{Cite news|url=https://www.newspapers.com/image/165555983/?terms=%22vincenza%2Bcarrieri-russo%22|title=AI Grad Receives Presidential Award|last=|first=|date=26 June 2003|work=|newspaper=The News Journal|access-date=|via=Newspapers.com}}</ref> In 2002, she co-founded the literacy organization Success Won't Wait Inc. when she was an 18-year-old high school senior and has been active in promoting literacy and has helped collect and redistribute over 600,000 books to communities, schools, and non-profit organizations in need.<ref name=":4">{{Cite news|url=https://www.newspapers.com/image/164582544|title=Poised for the Main Event|last=Mathur|first=Shruti|date=25 March 2008|work=|newspaper=The News-Journal|page=E1|access-date=|via=Newspapers.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newspapers.com/image/164582341/?terms=%22vincenza%2Bcarrieri-russo%22|title=Their Common Goal is Helping Others|last=Hoey|first=Kim|date=16 March 2006|work=|newspaper=The News Journal|access-date=|via=Newspapers.com}}</ref>
Carrieri-Russo competed in pageants for nine years prior to winning Miss Delaware USA.<ref name=":1" /> She was a three-time contestant in the [[Miss Delaware Teen USA]] pageant.<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newspapers.com/image/165526334/?terms=%22vincenza%2Bcarrieri-russo%22|title=What's Hot|last=|first=|date=29 September 2001|work=|newspaper=The News Journal|access-date=|via=Newspapers.com}}</ref> She also competed in the [[Miss Delaware]] America competition four times having placed in the top ten twice where she also won several community service awards. After her year as Miss Delaware USA, she went on to be named a top-six finalist at the annual Miss Italia USA pageant.
As Miss Delaware USA Carrieri-Russo participated in charity events including the [[Delaware Air National Guard]] Plane Pull for Special Olympics and continued to promote her Success Won't Wait program.<ref name=":4" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newspapers.com/image/164309894/?terms=%22vincenza%2Bcarrieri-russo%22|title=Pulling Together for Charity|last=Brown|first=Robyn|date=5 May 2008|work=|newspaper=The News-Journal|access-date=|via=Newspapers.com}}</ref>
In 2014 she opened the "Vincenza & Margherita Italian-American Bistro" alongside her sister Margherita Carrieri-Russo.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.delawaretoday.com/Delaware-Today/March-2015/V-M-Bistro-Knows-Italian-Food/|title=V&M Bistro Knows Italian Food|last=Amis|first=Mark|date=March 2015|work=|newspaper=Delaware Today|access-date=|via=}}</ref> Vincenza Carrieri-Russo is a third-generation restaurateur.<ref name=":2" />
Carrieri-Russo received a Presidential Student Service Award for her work with Success Can't Wait in 2003.<ref name=":3" /> In 2005 she became the first Delawarean to win the National Jacqueline Kennedy Onassis Award presented by the [[Jefferson Awards for Public Service]].<ref name="cjonline">Staff (June 21, 2006). [http://cjonline.com/stories/062106/loc_jeffawards.shtml#.VX4x6EN0knE "Jefferson Award Winners Announced"]. ''[[The Topeka Capital-Journal]]''. Retrieved June 14, 2015.</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.newspapers.com/image/163104653/?terms=%22vincenza%2Bcarrieri-russo%22|title=Delawarean highlights community service|last=|first=|date=22 June 2006|work=|newspaper=The News Journal|access-date=|via=Newspapers.com}}</ref> She was named as one of Delaware Today's 40 under 40 in 2008 and to their List of Women in Business in 2015.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.delawaretoday.com/core/pagetools.php?pageid=6574&url=/Delaware-Today/May-2008/40-People-to-Watch/&mode=print|title=40 People to Watch|last=Amis|first=Matt|date=May 2008|work=|newspaper=Delaware Today|access-date=|via=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.delawaretoday.com/Delaware-Today/December-2015/Women-in-Business-2015/|title=Women in Business 2015|last=Nardone|first=Mark|date=December 2015|work=|newspaper=Delaware Today|access-date=|via=}}</ref>
